The paper deals with power control in massive MIMO networks with distributed antenna arrays, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer communication (cs.COM). The paper specifically focuses on the impact of spatial separation between antenna arrays on power control, which is a key aspect of massive MIMO networks and falls under the purview of cs.IT and cs.NI. The proposed max-min power control algorithm also involves control systems and optimization techniques, which are relevant to cs.SY. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of power control on spectral efficiency, which is a key metric in multimedia and communication systems, and hence relevant to cs.MM and cs.COM.
